[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     816[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 7: Hybrid Integration with Recipe 7.11 XGBoost Score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The main recipe describes the hybrid pattern: primary XGBoost prediction plus similarity-based novelty flag and case-based explanation. Here we show how the two systems integrate. The XGBoost score from 7.11 is your primary predictor; this recipe's kNN layer adds self-awareness about what the primary model doesn't know.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def simulate_primary_model_score(claim: pd.Series, rng=None) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Simulates the XGBoost denial probability from Recipe 7.11.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, you'd call the SageMaker endpoint:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sagemaker_client = boto3.client("sagemaker-runtime")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         response = sagemaker_client.invoke_endpoint(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             EndpointName="denial-prediction-endpoint",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ContentType="text/csv",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Body=claim_features_as_csv
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     832[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score = float(response["Body"].read())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     833[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     834[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Here we simulate a reasonable score based on claim features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     835[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     836[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if rng is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     837[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rng = np.random.default_rng(0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     838[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     839[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Simulate: primary model gives a score based on features
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     840[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Novel payers get a "confident but potentially wrong" score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     841[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     base = 0.3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     842[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if claim.get("pa_required", 0) == 1 and claim.get("pa_on_file", 0) == 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     843[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         base += 0.4
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     844[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cpt_risk = CPT_CODES.get(claim.get("cpt_code", ""), 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     845[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if cpt_risk > 1.3:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     846[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         base += 0.15
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     847[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Add noise to simulate model uncertainty
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     848[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     score = np.clip(base + rng.normal(0, 0.1), 0.05, 0.95)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     849[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return float(score)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     850[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     851[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     852[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def score_claim_hybrid(claim: pd.Series,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     853[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                        claim_embedding: np.ndarray,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     854[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                        knn_index: NearestNeighbors,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     855[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                        history_df: pd.DataFrame,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     856[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                        payer_counts: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     857[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     858[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Full hybrid scoring pipeline for a single claim.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     859[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     860[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Combines:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     861[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Primary model score (XGBoost from 7.11)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     862[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. kNN neighbor retrieval and weighted vote
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     863[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Novelty detection from neighbor distances
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     864[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Routing decision based on confidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     865[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     866[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is what runs for every incoming claim in production.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     867[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     868[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step A: Get primary model prediction
